# Instagram feed slot climbing

When walking up from an `article` to collapse a wrapper, **sibling posts are often other `<article>` nodes**. `element.querySelector("article")` is **false** on an `<article>`, so peer detection must treat **`tagName === "ARTICLE"`** the same as “contains an article”.

Exclude the current branch with `c === el || c.contains(el)` as `el` climbs (not only the original `article`).

Cap climb depth (e.g. 6) so a bad heuristic cannot hide an entire column.
